                <fr:title text="Equivalent formulation of locality">Equivalent formulation of locality</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Remark</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>
  The following are equivalent for a distributive lattice <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex>:
  <html:ol><html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/idem-comm-75C1/" title="Local distributive lattice" uri="https://www.my-great-forest.net/idem-comm-75C1/" display-uri="idem-comm-75C1" type="local">local</fr:link>.</html:li>
    <html:li>The map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(-)=1 : D \to  2]]></fr:tex> is a distributive lattice homomorphism.</html:li>
    <html:li>There is a unique maximal ideal of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex>.</html:li>
    <html:li>There is a unique minimal filter of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex>.</html:li></html:ol></html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
